Citation.sTitle: Equilibrium Solubility of Sodium 2,4-Diaminobenzenesulfonate in Binary NaCl + H2O, Na2SO4 + H2O, and C2H5OH + H2O Solvent Mixtures at Elevated Temperatures from 273.15 K to 323.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of sodium 2,4-diaminobenzenesulfonate in binary NaCl + H2O, Na2SO4 + H2O, and C2H5OH + H2O solvent mixtures were measured at elevated temperatures from 273.15 K to 323.15 K by a steady-state method. The results of these data were correlated by a modified Apelblat equation.
